  "prompt": "Why is Quora still ad-free?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, Quora has implemented ads on its platform since 2020. However, the presence of ads can vary based on factors such as user location, specific content, or individual user settings. \n\nIf Quora continues to have an ad-free experience for certain users, it could be for several reasons:\n\n1. **User Testing:** Quora may be experimenting with different experiences for users to see how engagement changes with and without ads.\n\n2. **Content Focus:** In its early days, Quora emphasized a knowledge-sharing platform without ads to foster genuine engagement and high-quality content.\n\n3. **Premium Features:** Quora may be considering or offering premium subscriptions that provide an ad-free experience as a part of their monetization strategy.\n\n4. **User Feedback:** The platform might take user feedback into account when deciding the extent and nature of advertising.\n\nFor the most current information on Quora\u2019s advertising model or ad-free experiences, I recommend checking Quora's official announcements or their help center.",
